How to better prepare for the family photo session.
The summer is still in full swing, as is the next school year that families are able to capture in the memory immediately.
To make the photos look happy and beautiful, it is worth thinking about how to prepare for the photo session in advance.
The advice "Ihappymama" is given by many children's mom Aleksandra Nesterenko and professional photographer Marina Levickaja.
You have to take pictures in nature, because it is much more natural and harmonious.
The study makes it more difficult for children to get involved and relax.
It is recommended to choose a uniform dress style for the whole family, preferably in one color gamma.
For example, Alexandra says that she chooses clothing for all six members of her family so that no more than three colors and as little as possible inscriptions on the clothing.
Don't forget about a good mood.
Have fun, have fun, have fun, have fun, play, but never banish or psycho if children are not at once as obedient as they would like.
And here's the advice from the professional photographer's box!
You have to understand exactly what you want to capture during the photo session and tell the photographer about it.
For some they will be beautiful, children and an ideal family picture, for others - "life is what it is", i.e., the desire to see true, true emotions in pictures, or how to say the photographer himself in love - "vulnerable backs", "open eyes", "unlocked noses".
Of course, it happens that someone also wants "two in one", but this happens rarely.
In any case, when you go to the photo session, you have to understand that it's just a couple hours from your life, and the less you're gonna be stuck in, the better.
You're yourself, there's no strong mom who works, cooks, brings up and so on, and not the dad who's always talking on the phone.
And not the man who lives in you behind some unknown shell.
Be a family, remember how great it is to embrace one another, smile at your own people, and have fun.
And then the photographer's task will be just to capture the true moments of emotions that prevail among you.
If you have chosen a photographer, trust him.
Stop asking 250 times to show what has happened, to listen to his advice in choosing clothes, to better shots.
Fold and clean up all the clothes you need in advance so that you don't have to do it on the day of the photo session.
Plan the route and think about how long you will need to get to the place of the photo session (especially if photography takes place in a studio and time is limited).
If you have small children, then choose for the photo session the time that corresponds to the day-to-day period of the birth, so that it doesn't happen when your baby normally sleeps the day.
