The police rescue the baby from overheating in the car; the parents are threatened with judicial action.
In Riga, the municipal police rescued the baby from a hot car yesterday, while the child's parents threatened the police with judicial works about the lost glass of the car, LETA informed Riga Municipal Police (RPP).
Yesterday, an agitated man ran to the patrol, who told us that he noticed a car in a parking lot at Spice shopping center, where a baby was present for half an hour without adults.
On arrival, a car named by an eyewitness was found and was parked in the sun.
The front passenger seat contained the infant seat.
On the child was shined directly by the sun.
The infant shouted loudly, breathing intensely, and his face was reddened and flushed.
In view of the fact that the vehicle owner was not present on site, it is immediately decided to pull out the rear glass of the car in order not to endanger the health and life of the infant.
The child with the entire seat is taken out of the hot vehicle, and a medical doctor is called.
The child breathed shallow, the skin was red and hot, so until medical officers arrived, orderkeepers put a cool compress on the forehead.
Doctors and parents of the child came to the scene almost at the same time.
When the baby’s father saw the broken window on his vehicle, he remained aggressive and did not let the doctor come.
Discussions with parents have been carried out and it has been explained that a child under the age of seven is prohibited from being left alone.
In addition, the child was left in life - threatening conditions.
After discussions, the victims were examined and found that hospitalization was not necessary.
On the other hand, the child’s parents strongly refused to give any explanations about what had happened and threatened with judicial work on the car’s disintegrating glass.
During the discussions with the parents, there was no evidence that they were under the influence of alcohol or could otherwise harm the child.
The case materials were sent to the Children's Offence Prevention Department, whose employees will assess parental responsibility.
The RPP reminds us that even if the outside is not very hot, the sun - left car heats very quickly.
If a child or a pet is left in such a car, this may be a threat to their lives.
