Hillary Clinton stopped his campaign on Tuesday in Winwood, in the area of Miami, where there was an outbreak of locally transmitted Zika virus and put pressure on Congress to return from its five-week break in order to confirm the exceptional financing of the fight against the virus.
President Obama and the Congress Republicans have been in contradictions for most of the year on Zika virus issues.
