As a result of this impasse, the White House was forced to channel USD 589 million in April to fight against the Ebola virus.
On Thursday, Mrs Barvela said that her department had spent most of the money and that it would be fully spent by the end of August.
"The inability to decide on emergency funding for the fight against Zika virus has led the administration to choose between delaying the development of the important vaccine and taking over other valuable national programmes to avoid this delay temporarily," Barvela wrote.
