Last week, the National Institute of Health announced that it had started clinical trials of vaccine against Zika virus in 80 people and was looking forward to launching the second phase of "Zika virus epidemic countries" in early 2017.
However, as the officials claimed on Thursday, without immediate additional funding, the investigation will stop.
