A further 47 million will be transferred to the Biomedical In-depth Research and Development Authority, which supports the development of medicines and vaccines in response to public health emergencies.
This money will come from a number of accounts, including USD 19 million from a programme that grants subsidies for heating oil to low-income families and USD 4 million from substance-dependent programmes such as opioids.
