Shanghai, Taipei, despite the suspension of cross-border communication, will hold a forum
Shanghai and Taipei will, however, hold an annual urban forum in Taipei from August 22 to 23, and announced on Friday the municipality of Shanghai, despite the suspension of cross-border communication mechanisms.
High-level municipal official Sha Hailin Shanghai mayor Janga Xiong will lead the delegation represented in the forum, announced by the government of Shanghai in its official microblog account in Sina Weibo.
The Forum has been organised in rotation by both cities since 2010.
The 2016 Forum will focus on the exchange of experience in areas such as healthcare, electronic administrative services, culture and transport, seeking to "deepen the exchange of experience and cooperation in different aspects" between the two cities, as reported by the Shanghai Government.
