Ugandan President meets with Chinese Foreign Minister, hopes for closer cooperation
On Thursday, meeting with Chinese Foreign Minister Vangu Ji, Ugandan President Jover Museveni thanked China for its long-standing development support for Uganda and expressed hope for closer cooperation.
Museveni said that China was an ancient friend of Uganda and Africa who supported the release of the African continent from colonialism and later supported Africa's economic and social development.
The President mentioned the construction of the Tanzania-Zambi railway in the 1970s as proof of China's generous support, which was provided even when China itself was not particularly prosperous.
Museveni said that China has carried out multilateral cooperation with Uganda, both in terms of investment in infrastructure and entrepreneurship and cultural exchanges, and added that this kind of cooperation contributes to the long-term development of Uganda more than simply provided financial assistance.
He hopes that China will be able to participate in the development of Uganda's infrastructure and the construction of an industrial park in various ways.
He also calls on the Chinese to invest more in Uganda and travel around it.
Wang She praised Uganda's industrialisation and agricultural modernisation and added that China would continue to be the most reliable and ideal cooperation partner for Uganda.
Wang stated that China was ready to do its utmost to help implement Uganda's economic and social development and added that China's cooperation with Uganda was genuine and without any political considerations, as it was based on a high level of political credibility and proven friendship over time.
He said that China could strengthen cooperation with Uganda in the construction of infrastructure and industrial park and support the development of the energy and agricultural sectors of this East African people.
